reviews: This is a nice hotel in beautiful Bercy Village. Breakfast was ok, the staff not very friendly or helpful. The reception however is extremely nice and competent. The room we got was large and comfortable but a bit dated, especially the bathroom. This hotel is used for weddings and young people who book a hotel room during the weekend to party in the room and make a lot of noise. While people were polite, the noise and general party atmosphere made our stay a bit uncomfortable.

spent 5 nights here travelling from scotland with wife and teenage children. the hotel provided an excellent base for a superb visit to this amazing city. reception staff very friendly and helpful with the rooms serviced every day. nice leisure facilities to relax and recharge in. and the table tennis and table football facilities are a nice addition. we didn’t eat here but there are a full range of bars and restaurants a short walk away in bercy village. the nearby cour st emilion metro station is currently closed which is a little inconvenient. a very busy replacement bus service for the 14 line is the best public transport option to reach the hotel from gare de lyon station. there is the 24 bus service which stops very near the hotel. this connects to gare de lyon and has the pantheon as its terminus but we found this service a bit unreliable.

we had 3 nights in paris and had an amazing stay here - the rooms were lovely , bed was massive , shower was fantastic, the hotel is cool with funky touches throughout - the staff were always friendly and helpful through our stay - the new outside area unfortunately wasn’t ready on our stay but will be a great space when it’s open for use -
breakfast was always yummy and fresh would defiantly go back again and recommend to anyone
wi-fi signial also very good through stay

It appears communication from this hotel is difficult. Slow responses to emails, not addressing the problem raised. The hotel (and Accor) have a pricing policy that is completely flawed and yet they do not engage to address the issue.

Here is the problem.
The price of breakfast is Eur 29.5 per person (adult) per day. Children eat free. I got that much by email from the hotel when I asked.

However, the difference between the rate for a junior suite with breakfast and without breakfast is Eur 332.32 for 3 people - 2 adults and a child - for 3 nights.

Total for breakfast for 3 people works out to Eur 36.9 per person per day.

This means the hotel is charging for the child (should be free) and charging Eur 36.9 per person per day instead of 29.5. So basically it’s a rip off.

I have attempted to get some help from the reservations team directly. The reservations team only read the latest message and not the whole thread, and they have at no point addressed the inconsistency outlined above despite being asked multiple times by email.

I shall continue to escalate until someone from Accor or this hotel is gracious enough to get in touch with me.

I would recommend checking the rates offered by this hotel very carefully to avoid being ripped off.

Every time I am in Paris on business trip my first task is to book this hotel. For me it is the best in the area.

The rooms very spacious and comfortable. The service is excellent the breakfast is great.

Not in the centre of town but has great places to eat and good public transport links.

I have stayed at this hotel many times over the years, and have always been impressed with the service the staff provides. No matter what request I have, they are able to satisfy it, and do so graciously. The rooms are nice, although I must admit the suites are especially so. If you can afford one, I'd highly recommend booking it. The dining options are excellent, with a full hot breakfast buffet on offer. I really can't say enough nice things about this property, and consider it to be "my home in Paris".

I don't usually write reviews. My experience was mid to say the least. I can deal with the front desk clerks being selective with their customer service and I can even take their inconvenienced attitude towards being asked for help, but purposely not helping a customer is mindboggling.
My mother wanted to make sure we had a ride to the airport, so she asked the front desk the afternoon before if we could schedule to have a taxi the following day around 8:30am. The front desk person said they would do that without issue. The next day, we go down to the front desk and she asks if by chance they had called the taxi for us. The gentleman said 'oh sorry no taxis are running today'. He said there was a taxi strike yet there was no news of there being one. She then asked if there's another way to get to the airport and he says 'I don't know' and walks away. She then asked him if the train or metro line runs and he gave us 'the best route' for the train. It later turned out the metro were actually protesting that day and could have affected the lines he guided us to go on. Shocked by the lack of help, we walked out the front debating if we should run to the metro or take a chance on an Uber when a taxi pulls up to drop someone off. The drive gladly obliged to take us to the airport. Luckily we arrived, along with the rest of the thousands of taxis coming to the airport, in time to catch our plane.
Both my mother and I are not rude people and believe in life people help people, so we are still bewildered by the treatment. Overall, we enjoyed Paris and the amazing people who make the city great. However, it is sad experience made by one small clerk. I don't need a follow up with pretty words. I just hope our experience isn't the same for others.

Beautiful hotel
Breakfast service runs so smooth with excellent customer service ,we were made to feel so special and welcomed at breakfast
Location -multiple restaurants ,pubs,shopping right at the door step
Metro station -2-3 mins walk with great connectivity everywhere
Family friendly-staff always interacted with our toddler
Great spaces to sit around lobby
Reception staff always easy to approach and helpful
Great checking in experience
If we or anyone we know visit Paris again -we won’t be staying anywhere else
Only comment - please change carpets on the room they are quite old

Pullman Bercy
Overall not satisfied, the house keeping let it down big time.

1. Upon check in, the shelves, worktop were dusty, it’s visible and a layer to be wiped out, and my wife have to do it herself as the child is allergic to dust, not acceptable for not only Pullman standard but any hotel should have cleaned it when it’s clearly visible.

2. The hotel seems to be refurbished at some point as there’s many old obsolete fixtures around. The ceiling paint were peeling off and not very nice to look at.

3. The swimming pool has an one hour per guest rule and need to book in advance, not very easy to plan around when my family book this hotel because we wanted to spend time in the swimming pool. So an hour seems too little. There were a long queue to get in pool and staff clear pool by the hour, so if we turn up say 19.20, you only get 40 min to swim and will be asked to leave. Felt slightly pressured when I want to relax when staying in Pullman for a long swim.

4. The house keeping is not acceptable. Called 10min on phone with no answer, after requested for items, no show for 30 min and require 2nd and 3rd chase and even go down to reception in order to get what you needed. Felt like some very badly managed hotel. The front desk will simply said they thought it was dealt with already…

5. The washing product were never topped up. I stayed in the hotel for 5 days, they never top up automatically and must request and wait for 30 min to be dealt with. My wife was waiting in the shower for shampoo the first time round and ended up waiting for too long and have to come out and wait as it was way too long. And when the body wash ran out the next day, the house keeping came after serval chase, but do not think that it’s empty, as the bottle were stripped on wall, it’s not possible to tell how much it’s left other than keep pumping only only abit comes out every 6-7 pump, I gave more days to stay and must have this sorted out so I have to ask the maintenance guy to take it off physically from the wall to check until he realised two bottles were empty and then he replaced for us. There shall be under no circumstances a housekeeping staff confronting guest like this, just get on with work and check and change it! This is something I would never expect from a Pullman! Totally unacceptable!

6. Also when the housekeeping comes, they just knock once and let themselves in, my wife was in between shower as she was waiting and wasn’t wearing properly, but the man just came in even before we answered. His shoes also bring a lot of dirt inside and the towel by the bath tub were all marked. I understand we can use another towel inside, but the staff doesn’t seems to care in Pullman. My family is upset. If his shoes marked the towel, he can try to replace for us as I understand sometimes it’s unavoidable when it was dirty, but he just walk out after.

7. The key cards kept failing, I have to get card replacement serval times during stay as it fails to let me in room or to operate the lift. It is a recyclable card which is nice, but after going swimming, it’s half deformed and I have to wear my swimming gear to lobby to get a card replacement.

8. But the pool is quite nice, water was warm and I do enjoy swimming there despite the hour slot and over crowded queue.

9. For the bath rope, it was very nice that the house keeping took all our wet rope away, but no new rope been replaced. We have been asking for the 3 ropes replacement when we returned to hotel and caused delayed to our swimming slot. After 20 min we decided not to wait any longer as there’s only one hour pool slot. After we returned from swimming, only one rope was provided. Clearly staff don’t listen and doesn’t care, it’s totally not up to expected Pullman standards.

10. The cup in the room is not clean, the second day when I use the cup for coffee, I noticed the coffee mark ring in the cup from the day before. Obviously the house keeping just gave it a quick rinsed before placing it back on tray, that’s not acceptable for any hotel.

11. The basin and bathtub in room do not drain well, need to wait for water to clear a few time when brushing teeth and constantly standing in inches of water when having a shower. Wonder if the hotel management care the status at all? They charge a lot in peak season but not really getting it right.

12. The breakfast, I saw a fly trapped in the serving box crawling on the cooked fish. I have informed the staff and he had the fly removed by hand. And then closed the lid and left the fish for serving. And I have to ask the staff back and request the food to be replaced which he does after I made the point. Quite concerning with the level of hygiene of food.

13. The house keeping only remove items in the bin, other rubbish like empty used paper cups with coffee stains were left around. I am also into recycling but I don’t think I will reuse the used coffee paper cups and would expect housekeeping clearing them. Also there were metal spoon we used to ate dessert with chocolate and crumbs stuck on it, they were left on the TV table til checkout for 3 days! Does the hotel expect me to wash them?

14. I used the iron board for clothes and ever since it was left out by the window til check out. I expect every day I come back the room is made up in a presentable status similar to how it looks when check in. I don’t understand why Pullman expect otherwise. It looks bad and it’s danger to have the iron out when I have child staying in the room. If Pullman expect guest to pack themselves, I would expect a clear reminder so I know what to expect.

The list really goes on and this Pullman experience is not a nice one and I don’t think I would recommend to my friends.

Good location, near to subway station, close to restaurants and supermarket, good services and friendly attention. breakfast is a very good option to be added. It's an excellent hotel for families.
Is not located in the center of Paris but the mobility is easy and safety

My flight was cancelled and so I booked a room in PPC on booking.com for €217 but after payment was taken I got a notification to say that the hotel was fully booked (even though the money been taken from my account). I went back on the app and found it wasn't and a room at PPC was available but this time for €476.29. As I was desperate, as a single woman by herself, I reserved it and got a taxi straight to the hotel.

When I arrived around midnight, I was asked to do a pre-authorisation for €505 that was apparently declined even though it had been taken out of my account. I started to panic and burst out crying and the hotel staff looked at me blankly - offering no support. I asked to speak to the manager who was aggressive. Eventually, I was able to pay on my card (after working things out by myself and moving funds). This time it did go through on my card and the second pre-authorisation of €525 came out of my account.

The next day, I paid €505 for my stay (for one night!!) however the first pre-authorisation of €505 still remains on my account and hasn’t been refunded or returned over a week later!

As a young woman in Paris by herself at midnight - I was put in a vulnerable position where I potentially had nowhere to stay and felt like the hotel staff were not only unhelpful but also unkind. I've never experienced anything like it. I have filed a complaint today with Booking.com and await to hear their response.

We are staying with our three children for five days, and we must say we are very satisfied with the rooms (connecting superior) and the hotel as such (nice swimming pool). Clean and modern. We have only eaten breakfast at the hotel, but it has been delightful. Fresh omelet and a good variety of food. The hotel is situated a bit outside the center, but it has a nice little village just a few steps away. Here you can eat and shop, and you will also find the metro station St. Emillion. We have had no problems getting around seeing all the famous places. The staff is very helpful and friendly. Unfortunately, the hotel bar closes way too early! The hotel web site states that the terrace bar is open till midnight, unless out of season or bad weather. Not so, it has closed way earlier every night. Yesterday they closed just after 22, while kids still were running around playing and guests just came back from dinner. We had to visit another hotel bar in order to have a night cup. I think a hotel of this standard should be able to provide their guests with a bar service at least until midnight in the most busy tourist season.

Good stay in general.
Potential improvements: size of the beds, evening restaurant speed (we had to wait nearly one hour before getting any drink or food)
Positive points: service, localisation, breakfast quality

This hotel is located within walking distance to the concert place and nice little food village not far from Paris sightseeing center. They have professional and friendly staff and nice bar but asain food wasn't good here but cant complain since you are in France lol

Very dusty rooms. It actually make us sick. Check out the air con vent. The corridors also have a lot of cobwebs. When the manager is informed he promised to clean but nothing is done. How can a 4 star hotel have cobwebs!

Regret not heeding the advice of an earlier post.

Lovely location for our short city break in Paris. A very convenient spot to travel to from the Eurostar terminal, and great to get around Paris from. We did a day at Disney & saw all the sights from this location.
Staff very welcoming, friendly & helpful. Nice pool. Breakfast was expensive so we didn’t have it in the hotel.
Lovely restaurants nearby. Very comfortable rooms. Would definitely return!

It has been a couple years since I was last able to travel to Paris and stay at this wonderful property. The hotel itself is great - I would recommend booking a room on a higher floor for the best views. Yet what really sets this hotel apart is the welcoming staff. They are so willing to help in any way they can, and have always made my visits to Paris excellent experiences. Although I was away for two years, all the members of staff who were still working at the hotel remembered me and called me by name each time we passed. I see this hotel as being my home in Paris, no matter how often or infrequently I visit. I would immediately recommend this hotel to anyone, since as a result of being on Métro Line 14 it is very fast and easy to reach the centre of Paris. Yet the distance from the city centre allows the area around the hotel to be "Very Paris". There are plenty of friendly locals and lots of small colorful shops. I enjoy exploring the area around the hotel at least as much and sometimes more than doing that in the centre of Paris.

Very tiny room. We had a superior family room for 4 people and it looked more like a two persons room with two single beds! The beds were really small. There was also only two towels. We had to go to the reception to ask for more towels. After waiting like hours, we called again and they came with towels. We also wanted to use the microwave to warm food for our toddler.. the staff in the restaurant refused first to warm it up for us. I mean it doesn’t take any effort to warm something up. You also don’t get any parking deal by the hotel.

I booked the 1hr spa and 1hr candle massage.
The staff was very friendly, helpful and professional.

I 100% recommend the lomi lomi 1hr massage by William. The experience was great and took place in a comforting, calm, clean well-heated space. The massage was masterful and it is also quite an amazing rhythmic feeling that totally lulls you into a blissed-out state. I left feeling very relaxed, soothed and regenerated.

Wonderful experience at Sothys Spa at the Pullman. I was looking for a specific muscle recovery massage, and Elodie delivered perfectly. Beyond the wellness skillset, she had quite a good knowledge of deep tissue, which is often lacking in spas where pampering is the norm. I’ll be back!

Scrub + 90 min Swedish massage. Nice facility and comfortable tables. Melisa was very professional and exceptionally good at pinpointing my areas of stiffness and in need of focus. I was hoping for a lower cost per minute from the spa, but an excellent masseuse Melissa is. 😀

Had one of the best evening in my life. Jeremy was so knowledgeable and the cock tales he made me were out of this world. I'd defintely go back for some more, as long as I'm served by this lovely gentleman one more time 😉

My son and I were traveling and in Paris when he asked me if we could get a massage. After I got over my initial shock that my 19 year old wanted to get a massage, I thought it was a fabulous idea. My hotel recommended the Spa by Sothy’s. Booking was easy and fast and they got us in for same day appointments. Our masseuses were Melissa and Liane-they were both fabulous and super professional. The hour service left us refreshed and ready to tackle another few days of travel. I highly recommend this Spa. Safe travels.

room was nice . Team member was helpful and welcoming. The room service menu is quiet disappointing. Same apply for the bar: food menu . Selection is too small .The hotel location is very accessible .

Great location near the Seine and Bercy Village. Easy access by car or public transport. The room was amazing. Breakfast delivered in your room free of charge with delicious ingredients. Amazing!! Great for a family as there are a lot of games in the lobby

We cam from London by train to Paris and were quickly at the hotel from the main train station. The hotel is very nice from the inside with lobby bar, boutique shop and large lounge area with ping-pong table. The rooms were clean and nicely designed. The beds are very soft which gives you a good rest after an exhausting day of sightseeing. The hotel team is very friendly and helpful. We felt that they took good care of us.

this is a great hotel 3 minutes walk from the metro at Saint Emilion. You are right next to Bercy Village with great bars and places to eat. Great location for a visit to Paris as 10 minutes into the center but lovely and quiet. Great service and the best hotel Breakfast ever.

I enjoyed my stay at Pullman Bercy. We stayed here for my brothers 18th birthday gift and we were going to Disneyland for the day.
They upgraded his room for free which we appreciated. The rooms were clean and spacious- we would of appreciated a easier navigation of the tv in terms of languages.
The lobby is beautiful with lots of things to do- barber, nail technician and a bakery section.
The hotel was only 30minutes from Disneyland which was about 40-50 euros.
The hotel was around 25 minutes from the airport which was around 40 euros.
The shopping village next to the hotel was lovely. We ate at Vapianos and went shopping in Rituals and Sephora which added an extra layer of enjoyment to our trip.
I would definitely stay here again!

We had 3 nights in this hotel and it was like staying in two different hotels each night..
First night was amazing. Awesome service, great room service and breakfast was wonderful.
Second night was a disaster.. rude room service that evening and at breakfast the next day. Breakfast itself was poorly cooked - it felt like we were dealing with entirely different waiting and kitchen staff :(
Unfortunately as it was so inconsistent I would not take the chance again at staying at this hotel

Amazing hotel. It’s a bit far from the main attractions but we took Uber and it was just a beautiful ride especially while coming back in the evening when all the lights in the city are on. The next day we took Uber to notre dame which was only 10 euros and from there we took hop on hop off bus. Hotel is very clean and friendly. Dylan upgrade our room for free and he was very professional!
Night before my birthday amazing server Lea from the bar sent Champaign and cake in our room. I was over the moon. That was a real surprise.
Staff is definitely the highlight !
Would come here again for sure !

Encountered a good check-in, very engaging service - nothing was too much trouble for them and there was a great sense of welcoming a valued customer, irrespective of your nationality and language barrier.

I was issued a key-card (used to operate the lift and power room) and pointed to the lifts around the corner.

Thought the room was very good, large and spacious equipped with plenty of power points: beside the bed were a combination of UK, Euro and USB sockets (definitely had the international traveller in mind) with more below the desk. I'd prefer if they wall-mounted the phone, there's no reason it should take up so much bedside cabinet room!

Bathroom was clean, warm, functional, bright and nicely-styled - can't fault it. There's some pleasing views out the front but little noise; I had a pleasant night's sleep all nights.

Definitely a great stay away and I'll certainly welcome the opportunity of stopping here again!

First off, this is an impressive hotel as befits its price tag and star rating.

I was checked in by an extremely efficient and friendly person and offered a freebie glass of fruit juice and a chocolate biscuit by their equally friendly colleague. I was told they'd upgraded my room and indeed when I got there it was big, with two sofas, a double bed and a desk. Plus there were ample wardrobes, two fluffy towelling robes, and a huge TV.

All seemed in order. I noticed some ambient noise outside but ignored it; a city centre hotel will always have some kind of noise outside and some kind of clunking or grinding machinery indoors somewhere. I then ordered, and was brought by a delightful room service person, a burger and chips (excellent), some coffee (a cup, it was ok - I should have asked for a cafetiere), and headed off to bed.

And there was that noise. It was like the firing up and then down again of some machine, perhaps the aircon, perhaps some kind of waste processor. It was outside the room, but there was nothing visible when I looked. OK my fault - I should have said or done something about it as soon as I arrived at the room; I certainly couldn't be bothered to do anything then as I was in bed and about to turn the lights off.

Except...I couldn't turn the lights off. As usual in a hotel like this there were lights all over the place and at the bedside there were three switches. I turned them all off but some lights stayed on. I got up. I went to the door and turned off what was evidently the (only) master switch and everything was plunged into darkness. So I turned that back on to see what I was doing and make sure I didn't walk into the TV and then for about five minutes experimented with each of the other switches around the room to get all the lights off. I ended up by leaving one bedside lamp on, unplugging one of the lamps at the end of the room which stubbornly stayed on, and then turning the bedside lamp off from beside the bed. Surely a master switch by the bed would make sense?

Throughout the night there was the noise but it didn't keep me awake too much.

In the morning all was good, with a hot and powerful shower, plenty of towels, and an ok sink (square and shallow). On checkout the staff, yet again, were super friendly and helpful (I was walking to my meeting 25 minutes away).

So in all a great, "grown up" hotel and vrooming noise and light switches apart, not much wrong with it.

I would not recommend this hotel...you will receive conflicting information from the staff. Most of the staff are not friendly at all. There are better hotels than this hotel and at better locations. It is not value for money

I stay at this hotel at least a couple times per year for my leisure trips to Paris. I enjoy the location, as it's far enough from the touristy center of Paris to be relaxing, yet Métro line 14 makes reaching the first a ten-minute ride. (Note: because this is an automated line, it was operating normally during the recent transit strikes.) The hotel itself is quite nice, having undergone significant renovations in the common areas over the past few years. Yet, what sets this property apart for me is the staff. They are warm, welcoming, caring, and always helpful. I see this as "my home in Paris" as a result. I know beyond any doubt that the staff will make every possible effort to assist me, no matter what my request is. In terms of the accommodations, I'd advise booking a premium room if you are able, as the view from the upper floors of the hotel toward the city is beautiful. Highly recommended!

We stayed here for a couple days during the New years.

Lobby & service
I was pleasantly surprised when walking into the hotel, whereas the atmosphere / vibe was really relaxing and welcoming. So was the staff! Very helpful, respectful. They even remembered our names every time we passed the lobby.

Room
The room had decent space with a comfortable bed, the bathrobes were utmost nice compared to others I've had. The lighting in the room added to the pleasant stay as well. We asked for a baby cot and they took the liberty to think of any additional stuff we might need for our kid (baby tub, diaper bin and a teddy bear!)

Breakfast
Pullman hotel had an outstanding breakfast; serving a diverse set of warm food (eggs, beans and even chicken wings) to cold (yoghurt & sliced fruits).

Fitness
This hotel must have one of the BEST fitness areas I have ever seen in a hotel!
Hands down for their blessed fitness area!!!

Spa
Unfortunately the spa was under renovations so couldnt use this service. Read from other reviewers that it was closed a while ago so thought by time we reached we could use it again. Unfortunately the renovations were still on going.

Wouldn't mind staying at the Pullman Bercy again.

We stayed here during the Christmas break witha family of 5. We booked classic rooms. The hotel perfectly arranged 2 rooms with a connecting door. At arrival the 5th bed was not in the room yet. After a call the bed got installed. For Paris rooms are reasonable spacious, even with the extra bed you still could move around.
Staff is extremely friendly and helpful. The concierge (Hamid?) is brilliant, what an enthusiasm.
Hotel Lobby is an active area. Well designed and spacious, including two table tennis tables.
Location is great. Metro stops 4 minutes walk away and without many stops brings you directly downtown Paris. Hotel area is nice with Bercy village on 3 minutes walk.

Why only 4 points out of five. The room showed some small maintenance issues (loose wallpaper, damaged paint etc) and the breakfast was not great. Choice enough, but things were often cold and the breakfast space is too small. Despite the hotel staff is very friendly, they didn't pick up the phone when I tried to call the reception desk.

Conclusion: A few small things to improve to make it 5 points, but an absolute great hotel for visiting Paris. Better stay here than downtown. Will save you money and provide you more space and a very friendly staff.

Amazing experience at this hotel, from arrival to departure the team at Pullman has been a incredible help to us. The staff of the hotel is ready to provide any information that you need and they will sort out any problem. Staff is extremely kind and helpfull and the receptionist that helped us most of the time (Antoine) seemed not only professional but also actually interested in helping. The pullman itself is really good compared to the other ones in Paris and the location is great. Its about a minute away from the nearest metro (cour saint emilion, line 14) and the Bercy Village has most of your needs. The hotel is clean and provides most things you need, the minibar is free and there is a free Nespresso machines witch gets refilled every other day. The rooms are large have windows that can be opened, very comfortable beds and clean showers with rain shower system. The breakfast has way more than you can try during your stay. Our experience at this Hotel was amazing!

We spent a wonderful stay at the Pullman hotel !
We had booked a family room which was perfect for us and our sons, even if the room was a bit tiny with all our luggage pieces.
Breakfast was splendid, large choice which pleased all our family.
The concierge team was sensational helping us moving in Paris, with great advices, special mention to them !
Special mention to Alexandre which was so kind when we arrived late at night after a pretty long trip !
We’ll come again !

The member of staff in this restaurant called Jeremy was great, his service was excellent, very polite. Very helpful.
The whole experience bring in the hotel was very pleasant,
I would recommend this hotel for great stay

Very mixed feelings with this hotel . Room is clean bright and spacious ( junior Suite )
Check in was awful which has probably clouded ourstay . Lisi ? From the concierge was amazing , can not thank her enough for her care and energy . Avoid breakfast. Stone cold food and cold service to match . Variety was good but a cold egg and bacon is not appealing to me . Staff were not interested. If you are a fan of customer service this place based on our experience will disappoint. Location is convenient with metro 4 minute walk away . Could be a great hotel but the service level is very patchy . Would I stay here again ? Only if I was guaranteed that there had been some changes with the hospitality side.

Another terrific stay @ Pullman Bercy. Merci Beaucoup to the Front Office team who were wonderfully kind & helpful to me before & during my stay - especially Lise, Julie, Dylan & Concierge. Hotel looked lovely for Christmas. I look forward to another stay.

We stayed 3 nights in 2 rooms as a family of 5 (2 adults and 3 children.) Check-in was excellent - less than 5 mins, and the front office and postal services was helpful also. The restaurant staff were very professional and helpful despite being busy and there was a variety of food. Generally the the hotel was a clean and relaxing environment with good service, and the bar was chilled out too with good music. The rooms were stylish, spacious and well-appointed and the beds were great for my back and neck pain, with memory-foam pillows that helped too. There was a couple of instances of blocked sink, toilet and bath but the problems were resolved quickly and efficiently. The management listens and problem-solves without any dithering although I would say one or two members of staff would benefit from retraining, but as a whole the staff are professional, attentive and friendly.
The hotel location was also great being right next door to Bercy Village with shops and food places, as well as not too far from the heart of things in Paris - some 30 minutes train journey to the Eiffel Tower, Arc de Triomphe and Champs Elysee district. Also not a long drive to the Notre Dame.
Would definitely stay again.

Clean room. Bed is 2 twins that they separated for us. There is a bar that you enjoy. We stayed there our last night before flying home. Has a TV with many stations. There was no clock that I saw but I had my phone.

The Pullman Centre Bercy is conveniently located if your business is in the Bercy area. The hotel infrastructure is nice. Rooms are spacious and the design is modern. Wonderful gym. Food is expensive for its quality and service is very slow, inattentive and inefficient. Even when there is only a couple of clients in the lounge it would be annoyingly time consuming to get attention from staff. We observed several mice in the lounge. Staff informed us that it was unfortunately caused by the proximity to the river and that the hotel was taking measures against it.....

Upon checking into my room I noticed the room had a funny stale smell so I reported it and they kindly moved me to a new room. The second room was better but after 3 days I could barely speak as my throat was closing up and I was coughing up all sorts of mucus which was grey (TMI I know) I tried turning the AC unit off and the air vent still would trickle air through and therefore I called the maintenance guy to come and fix it. What he found in the air vent was shocking!!!!! The air filter was filthy and for 3 nights I had been ingesting this filthy air causing me to get very sick. I immediately addressed it with the manager on duty and he moved me to a new room and straight away I could feel the difference as the air was CLEAN!!!! The manager on duty was not very accommodating in taking care of the charge for the first three nights and said that it was not his fault the air vent was dirty and was trying to make me feel as if I was at fault for not reporting this sooner!!!! I told him that in most countries they would be begging me NOT to sue them let alone give me a free room (only for the 3 nights) The manager said that we are in a France and we are NOT the rest of the world. His tone was very offensive and unacceptable for someone in Customer service. He went by the name of Romain. I am sure they went on to sell this filthy room to another customer and would not be surprised if there are several other rooms like this.

Anyway. Just look at the picture of the air filter 🤬🤬🤬

Just returned from a night away in Paris staying at this hotel for my friends 40th birthdays.
We were upgraded to a 2 floor suite.
From start to finish all the staff were absolutely amazing and we couldn’t have wished for a better stay.
It’s a few minutes walk to the metro making it easy to get around.

Best night ever, bedding moulding to your body. Only downfall was room service breakfast! Breakfast in a box and item in there really not worth the price at all. Aside from poor breakfast the room was nice! I would come back but next time just have breakfast in the restaurant!

The staff is really nice (Benjamin) and the magician who is doing the balloons is incredible. It is worth going on a rainy or cold day to occupy the kids :) The food is good, and the cakes with a theme also.

We have visited this hotel in the past; service has improved once again, but the most amazing achievement is the renovation of the hotel lobby. In this lobby, you feel wellcome to do whatever you like: play table tennis, have a drink in the attactive bar, do some computer work, ... Guests seem to feel at home in this lobby.
The breakfast room can be busy at peak hours, but staff is extremely friendly and busy.

In the bar at the Pullman is always a good atmosphere and great service. This evening I was served by Sandeep, who was very friendly and thoughtful. Even learned new French! As a regular guest the staff does great effort to remember you by name which adds to the experience.

I visit Paris on a regular basis and this is the first time I have stopped at the Pullman in Bercy. For me and my family our stay was ruined by one member of staff who has no customer service skills at all. What made it worse was the fact we later found out she was the manager/supervisor of the cafe area in the foyer. She made us all feel uncomfortable and my wife felt intimidated. We came back to our hotel after a wondiful day in Paris to relax with lovely hot chocolate in our hotels cafe area (well this is what we thought we would do) on the way back we passed a lovely shop that sold different biscuits so we purchased some. Like you do in this wondiful city. On arrival at our hotel we sat down and ordered 6 hot chocolate just like the ones we had the night before. Whist we waited for our drinks we though we would try our recent purchase. Well what a mistake that was! The cafe manager sent one of her staff over to tell us off! Then she kept throwing dirty looks over our way every time she walked past. In the end I had to speak with the hotel manager who said we were more than welcome to relax and enjoy our purchase of a biscuit! Suprising our hot chocolate arrived late and was nothing like the one we had the night before. I would like to add the rest of the staff were amazing and it is such a shame they were let down by one individual.

Conveniently located to the Accor Arena at Bercy, the Pullman has comfortable and well equipped rooms. The breakfast buffet is excellent and I cannot speak highly enough of the catering staff who went to a great deal of trouble to provide for my various food allergies.

Friendly staff and English speaking, breakfast was great and they had a wonderful cafe with an amazing wine selection. The hotel is very clean and modern and walking distance to non-touristy cafes and a small grocery. The area seemed very safe and full of commuters and families. A great way to see the everyday Paris.

We visited in October half-term (M-F) with our children aged 1 & 5.

We arrived at 11am (3 hours early) but our room was ready for us!

The hotel has the wow-factor: very clean, lovely facilities, helpful staff, bar, restaurant & table tennis tables. The only problem was the swimming pool was closed (maybe for refurbishment). The free WiFi is easy to use and available in rooms, no need to keep logging in!

We requested a travel cot and when it arrived it was a a fully-assembled traditional wooden cot on wheels with bumpers, bedding, baby bath, changing mat and nappy bin.

There are tea facilities in room and a fridge which is refilled with Evian water every day. We used the fridge to store milk and beers from the Carrefour shop in Bercy village.

There are towels, flannels, robes and slippers in rooms!

Breakfast was perfect. Served from 6.30-10.00. All fresh and delicious. A wide variety of foods and drinks.

We happened to stay at the same time as the Rolex Paris Tennis Masters so there were professional tennis players everywhere. There was a great atmosphere! The event was being held at the Accor Hotels Arena which is next-door!

Bercy Village is stumbling distance and has lovely bars and restaurants, open all day and into the evening.

Taxis are always available from hotel. It cost €20 to Luxembourg Gardens. €60 to CDG airport.

It would take 2 hours to walk to Eiffel Tower (5miles) but following the river, you can’t get lost! Batobus hop-on boat speeds up the journey. There is metro station in Bercy Village.

Can’t fault this hotel 😃

Stayed for the weekend with the girlfriend and i cant fault it! From the check in to how clean the room was given to us. i would be recommending this hotel to friends and family. The staff was very friendly and helpful.
Thank you Pullman.

It is a very good hotel. However, the person who checked us in said we had not pre-paid for our breakfasts for our 6 day stay. According to Dylan, the person who checked us out, we had indeed paid. But we lost all those breakfasts because we went to a small bakery in the morning to avoid the nearly 30 dollars per person that they charge for breakfasts,.When I wrote a complaint to the hotel, I was offered points through Accor. I accepted the offer but never heard back from the agent who made the offer. A very disappointing situation given the level of the hotel, our long stay and the fact that we had a suite. If you decide on the Pullman, be aware that the check-in is problematic. And if they insist you did not pay for something, be sure to keep all your records and receipts close at hand to prove you did. If I hear back from the agent, I will follow up with another message to this site.

Excellent hotel. From the front desk to the restaurant, everyone is friendly and helpful. Our room was exceptionally clean and spacious. Very quiet, peaceful hallways which was nice for sleeping. Stayed here for three nights before heading to Normandy, would book again. The Metro is across the street which made access to the attractions easy.

Absolutely enjoyed everything about our three day break at the pullman.From the efficient welcoming reception to the spacious comfortable room. Immaculately clean toilets in room and reception.10 out of 10.
The Bercy village adjacent to the hotel with its numerous restaurants, shops and metrolink was very convenient, with the added bonus of security gaurds reassuringly making it feel safe and relaxing.
Nothing was too much trouble for all the reception staff from helping with sight seeing bookings to providing umbrellas on a rainy day and booking taxis, first class.
For 10 euros you can get a 24hr metro ticket which allows you to get to all the main Paris attractions within15 to 30mins of leaving the hotel.
The only down side is 3 days isn't nearly enough time to appreciate all that Paris has to offer, so we will be returning in the future. At the pullman of course.

Excellent hotel & wonderful loving staff which made hotel so enjoyable to stay at next to Bercy Village where you can experience the local activities among Persian & away from crazy tourists crowds... but my new friends from Pullman staff were certainly the heights and they made my trip much more enjoyable... I would like to sincerely thank Qi(Chi), Romaon & Monica to show thier sincere love, care and kindness and made us feel right at home... thank you guys for your love, respect & kindness...And see You Soon
Sincerely,
Mehran

At hotel for conference and seemed to have lost booking. Took an hour and half to check in - staff didn’t seem to care and required several reminders before checked in. Room was totally souless and without character. Fish and chips room service was v v poor. See pic. Basically fish fingers and cold chips with plastic cutlery for >€25. Do not stay or eat here. However area around Bercy metro looks great with lots of bars and restaurants.

My husband and I stayed here for two nights whilst on a longer trip in France and Italy. I booked via a secret deal so wasn't sure what to expect but I was blown away. The location is not central in Paris but the connection from main stations via the metro is easy and quick. If you don't know about Bercy village then check it out. The hotel is amongst restaurants and shops which was so convenient. The hotel itself is beautiful and the service is amazing. I booked two flights whilst there and staff printed out the boarding passes for me in an instant. Don't be put of by the distance from the centre. The metro ride is worth it.

Choosed Pullman when visiting Paris to celebrate a special occasion. The special welcome, the friendly and kind service at the reception, the beautiful and clean room with a magnificent view of skyline Paris, the symptous brakfast and the busy lobby bar...,all contributed to making our trip to Paris unforgetable. A big thank to all of you !

The hotel was comfortable and all the staff very friendly and always available to help and advise. Lise was extremely kind right from our check in. She went above and beyond to sort out our botched booking and was kind enough to book our activities for the week. She facilitated sight seeing trips, restaurant and cabaret bookings and ensured we knew how and when to get to each location.

Aurore was equally friendly and kind and was willing to answer all our questions and give directions. Hamid and Sandeep also helped to make our stay a pleasant one.

The nearby Bercy Village down the road has exceedingly convenient shops and a plethora of restaurants which proved very useful.

My husband and I would be quite happy to stay at the Pullman Bercy again and again.

My sister and I enjoyed a very comfortable 3 night stay at the Pullman in Bercy. Friendly and efficient check-in, spacious room with two double beds, excellent toiletries etc and efficient air conditioning (it was very hot outside!). It is only 4 stops from Gare du Nord - change at Gare du Lyon so very accessible. We spent our days in Central Paris and it was nice to spend the evening in Bercy Village where there are numerous shops, bars and restaurants within less than 5 minutes walk. The metro station is also in Bercy Village so again just 5 minutes walk from the hotel. We stayed at the Pullman in 2011 and hope to return next year. Excellent buffet breakfast with everything you could wish for! There was a mix of leisure travellers, conference delegates and business travellers in the hotel and this worked well. An excellent venue for a conference and I would guess much better value than in the city centre. Highly recommended!

The Pullman is a large modern hotel with everything you would expect from the brand. However, the clincher for this place is the nearby Bercy Village with chic restaurants, shops and a cinema. Close to Metro line 14 so everything going for it.

Arrived after a red eye. Was told the room was ready, but I couldn’t check in till 3pm- unless I would pay $89 euros or he would be happy to upgrade me to a nicer room for $50euros/night and he would give me free early check in. I own a hostel in Central America if I did that to my customers I would be out of business. Would never recommend this hotel.

My wife, daughter and I stopped here for two nights in August.
This is a modern hotel with chic interior, and fantastic staff.
The metro station is a very short walk away as is the funky Bercy village (shops and restaurants), which offers plenty of alternatives if you want to dine out locally.
Our room was smart and very clean with a very comfortable double bed. However our daughter's (less comfortable) fold-out bed did obstruct free movement, especially to the curtains and windows situated in the same corner of the room as that bed.

When we checked in to our room we found the air-con was off, with the digital thermostat showing the room temperature at 27 deg C. We immediately adjusted it as low as we could, but when we checked out two days later it was still showing an, uncomfortable, 23 deg. C; the hotel management needs to ditch the bogus environmental agenda and give guests the facility to cool down. The double-glazed windows didn't help, their inability to significantly suppress street noise perhaps evidencing poor thermal resistance too.

On the first night we were missing the towels etc. for the third occupant - we asked reception to correct this as we went out to dine, but it wasn't done. The chambermaid got it right the next day.

Breakfast was disappointing on both mornings. Coffee was served at the table from a single multiple choice dispensing machine (I would expect a proper coffee bar at this level) and was therefore watery and tasteless. The pastries were bland and stale - a poor imitation of those glorious croissants of old.

And then there is the parking! 78 Euros to park our car two nights. This is extortionate, regardless of whether the car is parked on the hotel's forecourt (as was ours) or whether it is parked in the hotel's "private" car par (which is, I gather, a reserved zone in the adjacent, public multi-storey car park). Had I had the forethought of using one of the parking apps on the internet I could have secured parking in the same multi-storey, for 60% of the price charged to me; still pricey but 40% less so - do your homework and avoid the rip-off.

On first encounter a lovely hotel, handy for transport, with great staff, in an enchanting area. However too many minus points; hot room, mediocre breakfast and nebulous and pricey parking arrangements.

This is a Modern hotel just slightly outside the tourist areas of Paris. The Metro is located directly across the street from the hotel (5 min walk). Within 15 minutes or less, we could be in any tourist area of Paris via the Metro. We also took taxis to and from the city for around 20 Euros when desired. The Bercy Village shopping and dining complex is right next door to the hotel and is a picturesque outdoor venue with good restaurants and shopping options.

The hotel staff was amazing!!!!! The Concierge, Hamid, worked persistently to help me resolve an expensive reservation I had missed. Everyone on staff was very professional. The bar and onsite restaurant were pleasant, and the breakfast Buffett was quite good. The rooms were clean and modern in style. The bathroom was similar in size to similar American chains. The hotel had an overall upscale feel full of modern touches.

We really enjoyed our stay and will return soon!

Recently stayed at the Pullman Paris Percy, which is located just outside central Paris.(3 metro stops)
Even though the Hotel is extremely large the customer service that all staff show us on our three day visit was very personal and helpful. Rooms are of a high standard and the breakfast offerings was of a high standard.

If I were staying in Paris again, I wouldn’t hesitate in booking once again at the Pullman Paris Bercy.

We stayed at this hotel in July 2019 and absolutely loved it. Once we checked in, we were upgraded to a duplex suite. The manager was kind enough to walk with us to our room and explain the various landmarks we were seeing from our room. The room was beautiful with an amazing view of the Notre Dame cathedral and the Siene river. The hotel is located very close to the Bercy village with lots of restaurants nearby. We loved the breakfast, staff was very helpful... We'll definitely stay at the Pullman - Bercy when we visit Paris again.

We stayed at this hotel in July. The rooms were bigger then I would have thought and 4 of us fit well with our luggage and my son sleeping on the floor (he prefers it to the bed). The only bad thing about this hotel is if you want to be close to the city of Paris, this isn't it. We would take the Metro every day into Paris, about 25 minutes depending on where you were going. Metro was very convenient, across the street. There was a nice outside village of restaurants, shops and movie theater across the street as well, so plenty of places of different places to eat from breakfast to dinner.

We stayed at the Pullman as a family of 5 in adjoining bedrooms for three nights. The rooms were spacious, comfortable (the bed in particular!) and spotlessly clean.
All the staff were very friendly and helpful. They helped us with advice on how to travel to Disneyland before we went and my daughter loved the free chupa chups lollies.
We were a bit disappointed that the pool was out of use and will be for the foreseeable future as it was such a hot weekend. But so much to see and do in Paris we didn't dwell on that for long!
The area was absolutely perfect. We loved Bercy village and ate most of our meals there.

It's our 2nd stay at the Pullman since the new opening. And it's always a pleasure to stay in this hotel. The staff is lovely, special mention to Benoît who give us a free upgrade in deluxe room.
Food is ok, room spacious and quiet.
The swimming pool was closed, we will have to wait until the end of the year.
Very good 4-star hotel in Paris.

Good location.... but the breakfast wasn’t special... scrambled eggs and bacon... poor and uncooked...
Room cozy and quiet... but non so clean...I found the toilet brushed full of....**** and the shower was clogged ...
Disgusting!

We are currently staying at the hotel. We checked in yesterday and it has been an amazing experience from the very moment we stepped in. We were greeted by the concierge - Aurore and she is a star! Our stay has been made special by the exceptional service of everyone. Fab hotel and the device is even better. Highly recommend.

We stay at June 26 for 3 nights at room 1008. We booked the duplex suites. Please avoid this hotel during summer and fall and heat wave!!!! They do not have AC. They only have air cooling. And the air that coming out from the “AC” outlet is veryyyyyyyy little of air. When we stayed over there, there were a heatwave in europe, so we sleep in sweat and cannot sleep until 3 AM every single night!!!! They know it is a common problem so they have a fan to cooling down the room, which did not help at all. The hot water in the room is also a problem. It is only HOT water. No warm/cold water in the shower. Be carefull with this, can scald your skin!!! They just waiting a lawsuit happening to this hotel. We try to look for different hotel (avoiding accor hotel even though i have a platinum accor membership), it was hopeless because it is a high season of traveling in europe. So most hotel that accomodate family is fully booked. Next time, we will avoid all accor hotels in paris except during winter. Most of their hotel is ONLY have air cooling. Not Air conditioned!!

We stayed here for 3 days prior to a trip further North. Lovely location outside of Paris, close to the train and next to lovely Bercy Village and Park. Our server, Sandeep, was kind, friendly, always smiling, and was more than happy to make sure we had drinks and snacks! Since our stay was during a terrible heat wave, having a refreshing cool drink outside or in the lobby was wonderful!

Le personnel est souriant, content et serviable. C’est très agréable. Employees are relaxed and hard working and happy to serve and to help. It ‘makes A very pleasant change to many other hotels, especially parisien hotels and restaurants!

This is such a nice hotel , newly renovated in Pullman Bercy. Reasonable and very close to Saint Emillion which offers EXCELLENT connections to the center of the City where you will need to go everyday.
For Food, there is the Bercy Village and I loved the Restaurants there. Vapiano is great on the great. A Nice fresh live Pasta stations.
In the Hotel there is a pool and a spa. The food is not the best at the hotels restaurant you are better off eating at Bercy Walk.
The concierge Hamid was awesome in giving advices. He guided us to Montemarte which was not on the plan and it worked out very nice.

We chose this hotel for our trips to Paris and it was a first for us, since we had never stayed at a Pullman before. Our choice was smart, ultimately staying here was a pure joy. The feeling we had from the very entrance was that of a comfy, modern structure, inspiring vibe, good karma, awesome smell. The suite we were assigned left us speechless (located on the 10th floor and actually built on two levels). It was provided with basically everything you need (we compared it to Sofitel and Radisson we usually stay at) and it had the most amazing view! The location of the hotel is perfect, no surrounding street noise, the sleep quality was great, the spaces exceptionally clean and luminous. The breakfast selection was generous, everything you could think of in terms of morning appetite was actually there. Mr. Hamid, we kindly thank you for the upgrade on the occasion of our double anniversary and for going to so much trouble preparing our surprise, for the delicious chocolate cake and for the truly warm and professional welcome we had at the reception. Our appreciation also goes to Maria, your Romanian employee covering the night shift; she was extremely kind, professional and helpful. I truly recommend this hotel, for everything it offers, we will most definitely choose a Pullman again for our future trips. UN GRAND MERCI donc, à vous tous, c’était un réel plaisir de vous connaitre et d’être logé dans cet hôtel tout à fait nouvel et surprenant pour nous.

We stayed 2 nights at the duplex suite. And all I can say is that the way the staff treated us was beyond our expecations. Super friendly and service minded. The rooms was clean and spacious. Good for families. Not a typical familiy hotel but that I was aware of. The only drawback was that the pool was closed. But the staff aranged us a good deal that we were happy about. Highly recomended. Close to metro and good restaurants.

Stay in January for business and it's all in very good measure ; good Breakfast, large room , good Bathroom , good service , i didn't use the pool , i didn't know it was there ..
in whole a great experience

My fiancée and I stayed at this beautiful hotel for her birthday. The staff were very kind, they put some candies and a ballon in the bed. All was very clean and neat. This is our 2nd time at the PULLMAN Bercy and we highly recommend it.

Pullman Bercy is a good option for a central Paris stay. Not over crowded and no too far from most of the main attractions.
I arrived early on the day of check in and opted for the 50 Euro early check in fee - it was worth it to recover from the 24 hours in the air.
The check in staff were very friendly. I had been practicing my French, but it never comes out right when you need it the most - she was very understanding and patient as I "practiced" my French with her!
The food was OK. Breakfast buffet was a bit repetitive, but was well prepared and tasty.

This was our first stop on a EU Road Trip from the UK, destined for Malaga and what a fantastic stop it was. Traveling with two young children for days on end in a car is not easy, so the evening stops are always very important. I had stayed in this hotel before on business and when I was looking for a Paris stopover, it seemed like a good opportunity to re-visit based on the hotels excellent location, parking facilities, nearby park and Metro stations. I could not find fault with anything. The staff were warm and welcoming and even coped brilliantly with my two young boys who were over-excited having only just been released from a 5 hour drive. The family room was excellent consisting of two double beds and brilliantly appointed bathroom with all the in-room creature comforts. My wife became particularly attached to the in-room Nespresso machine. Bercy Park next door was a great place for the kids to roam free and the Metro station gave us excellent access to the city centre for a lighting tour of the sights and attractions. In the evening the kids loved the swimming pool and breakfast the next day was superb, and really set us up nicely for our days driving to the Spanish border. Thank you Pullman, you were a great start to our holiday.

Main reason for our stay was to watch a show in the nearby Accor Arena…
I write this article as a Platinum member.
Arrival into Paris with our private car was fine. Parking at the hotel is very difficult, even just for check-in.
Only two check-in counters were available with a view people waiting.
When it was my turn, I presented my booking details as well as my platinum membership card.
No greetings as a loyal member was given, as well as no upgrade. Even for the welcome drink vouchers I had to ask at the end of check-in.
So the check-in experiences, compared with other Pullman hotels, was not so good.
Our room was a family room with two big beds. Nice and clean perfect for our stay.
I made my self a cup of tea, before we left for the show. After we came back we discovered, that the water kettle was spoilt and water was leaking all over the area. Spilling water on some of my documents and my mobile phone, luckily the phone was still working. The kettle was exchanged after we complained to the front desk, but when we returned to the room after dinner the next problem happened. Our room was without power. So I had to go back to the front desk, to ask for help again. We had to wait for 15 minutes till somebody came up to the room, just to check on some fuses, which caused the problem with the power fail.
Next morning we went for breakfast around 09:30, hopping to avoid the big Chinese’s travel groups, but unfortunately they were still there. So we had to wait for a table and it was very load. Once we had a table, we discovered, that a lot of breakfast stuff was not available. For example the complete tea section was out of stock, glasses were missing at the juice section and lots of food was not available. So the breakfast experience was not very pleasant and we were looking forward to it, because we read, that Pullman has one of the best breakfasts in town.
After my breakfast, I wanted to collect my tickets for a river cruise on the Sein, which I was included in my room package.
Unfortunately the tickets were not ready yet and I was ask to wait another 30 minutes, before the responsible person would arrive.
Of course I don’t wanted to wait again, so we left without the tickets and bought them latter on directly at the cruise company. At check-out we were reimbursed for the tickets and the room rate was reduced as well for one night to compensate the price different. This was nice of the hotel, but still I can’t believe a 4 star hotel can’t even handle a sim

Room was ok, hotel in general looks ok, but the staff deleted all that and more...rude unhelpful and ignorant...goes out of their way to ignore you and make you feel like an idiot standing there..obviously whoever is in charge of restaurant/bar staff should be replaced with someone that can train staff and let them know their guests pay lots of money to stay there and should be treated accordingly..impossible to get a drink..reckon I could stay there all day and no one would talk to me..at the second go the bar staff in middle sentence taking order turned around and had a shot and celebrated with other staff...???! Need I go on...there was some kind of a arty farty do on, taking up the entire bar, and their little coupons were very important whilst totally ignoring paying guests..
At breakfast tried for about 20 minutes to get coffee....but noooooo.....not possible,,.one (that is 1) woman(slowest in history, walking slowly and chats away with staff) goes around takes order from one table, then goes back herself and makes the couple of coffees and delivers them herself...can I remind you this is a BIG hotel, lots of people waiting for coffee I’ll tell ya....and breakfast was rubbish overall anyway...not just saying that because I’m disappointed, was just not very good food, fresh french bread yum, not here I’m afraid...so yes, goes without saying, not going back to Pullman Bercy ever

We have stayed twice at the Pullman Bercy. We cannot fault it. The staff, especially Hamed, are lovely and make you feel very special. We treated my Dad for his birthday to a weekend in Paris, but the hotel made it even more special. He returned one day to balloons and cake. We also was made to feel special, as we have a baby boy on his way, and we returned to balloons too !
The location is great. Very close to the metro and some lovely bars and restaurants. Room are very clean, breakfast is lovely, bar area is welcoming and the beds are extremely comfortable. We will return.. next time with our baby boy.

The best hotel in Paris! As an accor club member you are threated here with many extra's.
The rooms are very clean, breakfast buffet is very various. Only good things to say and certainly worth to recommend it.

I concur with all the positive comments about the interior and service of the hotel. However, I had poor nights of sleep because the room temperature was too high. Airco couldn’t be set any lower and there were no windows to open. In addition, I had a wifi access point next to my bed and during the night it was like a sparkling Christmas tree. Very disturbing. So not sure whether I will ever return.

We travelled as a group of 8 this weekend. We had a fantastic stay . it really is 5 star. Quirky modern and feels very new. Staff were so helpful in all departments and very friendly. The rooms were super 2 very comfy double beds in each room.the bathrooms were the last word with everything you could ask for. The location was also great with metro and bus stop on the door step.Breakfast was really nice with great variety something for everyone. Really nice new swimming pool and leisure facilities. Everyone in the group really enjoyed every aspect of this fantastic hotel in a fantastic city . don't stay anywhere else. Trust me!! Thank you everyone at Hotel Pullman Bercy.

Stayed there twice on our holiday and both times we were treated wonderfully. The hotel itself is beautifully decorated and the rooms, especially the large beds, were very comfortable. Close to the supermarket and a whole group of cafes and restaurants, clothes stores and the metro all a 1 minute walk away. At the other side of the hotel is a bus stop that takes you to many places around Paris. The public transport is very good also but keep in mind you have to pay on the bus with no change given. Would stay here again definitely.

Good hotel . We liked the hotel and room and breakfast was good as expected . Metro is just walk away and there are lot of restaurants nearby . Hope to visit soon . The river is close by the hotel . A walkaway will give all the details surrounding .

3rd time staying here on business as location is good, next to Cour Saint Emilio metro station and Bercy Village is only 2-3 minutes walk where lots of restaurants and nice boutiques for you to browse around after lunch or before dinner. The room is spacious with very comfortable bed and great pillows. Overall service is friendly and efficient especially thanks to Roxane at front desk who offered extra help when we needed. Cheers to the service team!!!

Location: near metro and Bercy Village (which has Carrefour, shops like Sephora, cinema and eateries).

Check in: was ok, we were served by Qi.
Room: very decent size, we appreciate having proper desk and lounge sofa. The shower is great, hot shower is wonderful especially during cold weather! Would have been perfect if they installed proper shower glass door instead of half shower panel. You can get some water splashed onto the immediate bathroom floor area. There was also no room slippers provided, which was slightly disappointing.

Do not disturb door sign: we had hung this at our door but returned to find someone had entered our room to leave some pastries for our stay. The kind gesture is well noted BUT the fact that your hotel staff had disregarded the door sign and gone in, says alot. My husband had left his phone in the room and was very relieved to find it still there while we were processing the shock of having someone come in like that. This should not have happened. It left a sour taste to our otherwise alright stay.

The hotel is just on the river siene an is just 59 minutes by airport metro station .

The checkin formalities are fast and superb.

The hotel offers good rooms and clean and neat as well as given great feeling.

The breakfast menu is simply superb and offer wide range for asian travelers..

The lobby is a place where you can hang around , play games like TT, surf on computers, sip a coffee leisurely,
just a morning walk on river side is really great.

The place is close to bercy village where market as well restaurants are bubbling with activity.

We got a deal on this hotel for a long weekend in Paris, could not fault it. Staff friendly and accommodating, rooms very comfortable with a range of amenities, powerful shower and rooms serviced every day. Large comfortable bed and pillows and quiet on the 7th floor i.e. no street noise.

Metro close by so no problem travelling about Paris.

In my opinion, the rooms are still the best deal in Paris, with one of the better beds in the industry.
But after almost 20 years of fidelity to Sofitel/Pullman Bercy I have recently been very disappointed.... After a few years of the new lobby concept, I am still not convinced by the check-in counters : when there are a lot of people, you don't know where to wait and people sometimes cut the line, pass in front of you, etc... But worse is the new remodelation : such a long work for... that ??? The new lobby bar looks like a train station hall : cold, noisy, ugly... You don't feel well, no separation between tables, no plant, just this horrible open space that makes you consider Starbucks Cafe 5 stars ! Death penalty for the architect ! Even the drink menu is ridiculous : 19 euros for a glass of basic so-so Champagne (this is more expensive than in some 1 star Michelin restaurants I know !) and 60 Euros for the double dose glass !!!! The hotel director's calculator was broken that day ! LOL. They almost have no classic aperitif drinks (5 choices), not even a bottle of red Port wine, which for me is a crime at the bar of a so-called 4 stars hotel ! The new color on the lobby walls is really ugly (a sort of dark brown) and there are 2 ridiculous ping pong table as working tables in the business area, which is totally open and in the middle of the path between the bar, the lobby, the restaurant and the elevators : good luck to try to concentrate and work ! Ok, I am sure they think all this is design and trendy, but I don't think they considered 1 only minute the clients comfort and well being. Then, such a waste of money and works disturbances during almost 1 year for that is a pity.
Luckily, the restaurant offers a short but interesting menu with excellent plates and a good wines selection. And the most important, the rooms are very comfortable, well equipped and soundproofed. The staff is also very attentive and friendly.
And for all that, I stick on my 4 stars rating, but would have given a 3.5 if available for all the nice moments I had at the old bar and that I will not be able to enjoy anymore.

I was there for 9 days. The staff were extremely pleasant and very helpful. I was there on business and it was close to my office. It is not located well for the touristy sites, but a very charming neighborhood.

Obviously, they had some renovation going on, and it was not finished in November. The new Bar was open.

It could be seen as a bit cold, but sharing a drink with some friends, we realised that it was a nice place to stay. Good service for cocktails.

However, we waited too long for our Burgers, I think they were still trying to find their way, just a week after the opening.

The rooms are ok, nothing special. Comfy bed, nice view, clean, smells nice.

Disappointed by the breakfast, too busy on Saturday, waited 15/20 min for a cup of tea. I believe they're victim of their success. Honestly I had better Breakfast buffet (Sofitel in Hamburg) for example. This is just average, and poor compared to prices.

Overall, it's a nice place, but don't choose it for its breakfast, way overvalued.
